{#-
  Nav-Header — page-level top navigation pattern (Ring 3 S3.2).

  Foundation pattern for the Nav family. Composes NavigationMenu Ring 2
  (primary nav, with optional Nav-MegaMenu items for multi-column
  dropdowns) + brand block (consumer-driven logo) + utility cluster
  (consumer-composed search / notifications / user menu).

  Below 768 px, the primary nav hides and a hamburger button appears
  that opens a consumer-instantiated Nav-MobileDrawer via cross-
  controller compose : `data-controller="drawer"` + matching
  `data-drawer-target-value` on both this header's hamburger and the
  consumer's Nav-MobileDrawer root.

  Composition pattern — Twig {% include %} with blocks (mirror
  `_auth-shell` precedent verbatim):

    {% include '@theme/components/nav-header/nav-header.html.twig' with {
      htmlId: 'app-header',
      ariaLabel: 'Principale'|trans,
      sticky: true,
      mobileTriggerControls: 'app-mobile-drawer',
    } %}
      {% block brand %}…consumer logo…{% endblock %}
      {% block nav %}…NavigationMenu items…{% endblock %}
      {% block utility %}…search / bell / user menu…{% endblock %}
    {% endinclude %}

  Parameters:
    htmlId                  (string, optional)  — auto-generated
    ariaLabel               (string, optional)  — default 'Principale'
    sticky                  (bool, optional)    — default false ; sets position:sticky
    mobileTrigger           (bool, optional)    — default true ; show hamburger < 768 px
    mobileTriggerControls   (string, required when mobileTrigger=true) — id of the Nav-MobileDrawer
    className               (string, optional)  — extra utility classes

  Blocks:
    brand    — consumer logo / wordmark (top-left)
    nav      — NavigationMenu items (hidden below 768 px)
    utility  — search / notifications / user menu cluster

  Accessibility:
    - <header> landmark
    - <nav aria-label> on the primary nav
    - aria-current="page" stamped by consumer on the active nav item
    - aria-controls + aria-expanded on the hamburger trigger
-#}

{%- set htmlId                = htmlId                | default('theme-nav-header-' ~ random()) -%}
{%- set ariaLabel             = ariaLabel             | default('theme.nav.header.aria.label'|trans) -%}
{%- set sticky                = sticky                | default(false) -%}
{%- set mobileTrigger         = mobileTrigger         | default(true) -%}
{%- set mobileTriggerControls = mobileTriggerControls | default(null) -%}
{%- set className             = className             | default('') -%}

{%- set _classes = ['theme-nav-header'] -%}
{%- if sticky -%}{%- set _classes = _classes | merge(['theme-nav-header--sticky']) -%}{%- endif -%}
{%- if className -%}{%- set _classes = _classes | merge([className]) -%}{%- endif -%}

<header class="{{ _classes | join(' ') }}" id="{{ htmlId }}"{% if sticky %} data-sticky="true"{% endif %}>
  <div class="theme-nav-header__inner">
    {%- if block('brand') is defined and block('brand') is not empty -%}
      <div class="theme-nav-header__brand">{%- block brand -%}{%- endblock -%}</div>
    {%- endif -%}

    {%- if block('nav') is defined and block('nav') is not empty -%}
      <nav class="theme-nav-header__nav" aria-label="{{ ariaLabel }}">
        {%- block nav -%}{%- endblock -%}
      </nav>
    {%- endif -%}

    {%- if block('utility') is defined and block('utility') is not empty -%}
      <div class="theme-nav-header__utility">{%- block utility -%}{%- endblock -%}</div>
    {%- endif -%}

    {%- if mobileTrigger and mobileTriggerControls -%}
      {% include '@theme/components/button/button.html.twig' with {
        variant: 'ghost',
        iconLeading: 'menu',
        ariaLabel: 'theme.nav.header.mobile-trigger.open'|trans,
        className: 'theme-nav-header__mobile-trigger',
        attrs: {
          'aria-controls': mobileTriggerControls,
          'aria-expanded': 'false',
          'data-controller': 'drawer',
          'data-action': 'click->drawer#open',
          'data-drawer-target-value': mobileTriggerControls,
        },
      } only %}
    {%- endif -%}
  </div>
</header>
